Key Match Events: Will Smith hit a tying, two-run homer
Kiké Hernández singled and took second when Andy Pages reached on catcher’s interference
Ohtani singled and Hernández scored on an error
Pages added a two-run, two-strike, two-out homer in the eighth
Post-Match Reflections: Shohei Ohtani expressed his desire to continue playing well in the post-season
Dave Roberts praised Ohtani's performance and the team's overall season
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was played in front of a sellout crowd of 52,433, including retired Dodgers star Manny Ramirez
The Dodgers will head to Colorado for a three-game set to conclude the regular season
Others: The Dodgers improved to 95-64 and will open the playoffs on Oct. 5 at home in a best-of-five Division Series
Freddie Freeman sustained an injured right ankle late in the game
